properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 3 at 1:09PM PST until February 5 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM TO IMPACT THE REGION BEGINNING TUESDAY AFTERNOON
THROUGH EARLY WEDNESDAY EVENING...

.A storm system will move into the region Tuesday afternoon.
Abundant moisture will result in heavy amounts of snow for the
mountains and high valleys before snow levels rise and
precipitation changes to rain.

* WHAT...Snow expected below 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 4 to 8 inches inches.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...From 1 PM Tuesday to 7 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM TUESDAY TO 7 AM PST WEDNESDAY FOR WESTERN KITTITAS COUNTY BELOW 3000 FEET
